 Data Scientist (Weather and Climate) â€“ Digital Farming (2101220) â€“ Research Triangle Park, NC 
 Where the Chemistry Happens 
We are currently seeking a data scientist like you to join our Digital Farming Weather team in enabling farmers to improve and automate agriculture through advanced models, smart sensors, and artificial intelligence. Together with the agricultural and remote sensing R&D teams, we co-develop weather and agricultural data-driven solutions for addressing todayâ€™s complex crop production challenges.
 Qualifications - BASF recognizes institutions of Higher Education which are accredited by the Council for Higher Education Accreditation or equivalent 
Formula for Success
 Leveraging your education in the earth sciences, computer science, or a related discipline and your professional work experience in data science, including data wrangling, statistical models, and machine/deep learning, you will create novel hyperlocal historical and long range forecast agrometeorological data products. 
 Being well-versed in the Python data science ecosystem (NumPy, pandas, Dask, Jupyter, scikit-learn, PyTorch), geospatial libraries (rasterio, xarray) and formats (GeoTIFF, NetCDF, Zarr) as well as AWS cloud technologies (S3, EC2, lambda, SageMaker), will serve you well as you accelerate innovative weather and climate solutions across Digital Farming application areas. 
 Applying your knowledge of software engineering best practices, you will assist in data engineering of weather and climate data pipelines as well as in the serving of analysis-ready weather data to the R&D communities. 
 With your experience in statistical data analysis and data visualization, you will also perform weather and climate data analyses as well as create associated data visualizations to support organizational decision-making and product initiatives. 
 Using your good project management skills, you will work with stakeholders including the product, data and design teams to set project objectives, timelines as well as delivery pathways. 
